  "doc_id": "44546",
  "text": "We localised ß-NAG and ß-GLU enzymes in embryonic chick whole lungs at incubation days 7, 9, 11, 13 and 18. The ß-NAG staining was assayed according to Hayashi's method (1965) . Briefly, sections were immersed in 0.1 M Na-citrate buffer, pH 5.2, containing 0.25 mg/ml Fast-Garnet GBC (Sigma-Aldrich, F-8761) and 0.2 mg/ml naphthol AS-BI N-acetyl-ß-D-glucosaminide (Sigma, N-4006) for 1 h at room temperature. Some lungs were stained in toto for ß-NAG. The ß-GLU staining was assayed as described by [CITATION_1] ; the sections were immersed in 0.1 M Na acetate-acetic acid buffer pH 4.5, containing 0.3 mg/ml Fast-Red GG (Sigma, F-7013) and 0.28 mg/ml naphthol AS-BI N-acetyl-ß-D-glucuronic acid (Sigma, N-1875) for 3h at 37°C. Controls of b-NAG reaction were determined in 0.1 M Na-citrate buffer pH 5.2; controls of b-GLU were determined in 0.1 M Na acetate-acetic acid buffer, pH 4.5.",
  "correct_citation": {
